}
2. Reverse Pattern
Example 1
* * * *
* * *
* *
*

Code:

for(int i = 4; i >= 1; i--){
    for(int j = 1; j <= i; j++){
        System.out.print("* ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
Example 2
4 3 2 1
3 2 1
2 1
1

Code:

for(int i = 4; i >= 1; i--){
    for(int j = i; j >= 1; j--){
        System.out.print(j + " ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
3. Key Logic (Understand this or quit now)

Every pattern has:

Outer loop → rows
Inner loop → columns

Example:

for(int i = 1; i <= 4; i++)   // rows
for(int j = 1; j <= i; j++)   // columns

👉 If you don’t understand this, you will fail pattern problems.

